.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "January 2026" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a basic UNIX command line interpreter that reads commands from standard input
and executes them.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes. It supports
executing commands using absolute paths or by searching the PATH environment
variable.

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell.

.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:

.nf
$ ./hsh
($) ls
file1 file2
($) exit
.fi

Non-interactive mode:

.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
file1 file2
.fi

.SH LIMITATIONS
This shell does not support pipes, redirections, command chaining,
or built-in arguments.

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns the exit status of the last executed command.
If a command is not found, the shell returns 127.

.SH AUTHOR
Patrick Macabulos
